Package: rmachines
Type: Package
Title: rmachines: An Ensemble Modeling Package using Random Machines
Version: 0.1.0
Author: Mateus Maia and Anderson Ara
Maintainer:Maintainer: Mateus Maia Marques <mateus.maiamarques.2021@mumail.ie>, Anderson Ara <ara@ufpr.br>
Description: 
    The "rmachines" package introduces a novel ensemble method employing Support Vector Machines (SVMs) as base learners. This powerful ensemble model is designed for both classification and regression problems, offering versatility and robust performance.
References:
     - Ara, Anderson, et al. "Regression random machines: An ensemble support vector regression model with free kernel choice." Expert Systems with Applications 202 (2022): 117107.
     - Maia, Mateus, Arthur R. Azevedo, and Anderson Ara. "Predictive comparison between random machines and random forests." Journal of Data Science 19.4 (2021): 593-614.
     - Ara, Anderson, et al. "Random machines: A bagged-weighted support vector model with free kernel choice." Journal of Data Science 19.3 (2021): 409-428.
